\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527948\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gox1665702984604.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gox1665702984604.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gox1665702984604.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gox1665702984604\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Uniface Index Color Mnemonics\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Color mnemonics in the table define the 64 Uniface index color combinations.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gox1665702984604__section_unk_mcn_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d627400e51\">Arguments</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5588e1_d5589e1_d5590e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Mnemonics for Uniface Index Colors</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5588e1_d5589e1_d5590e1__entry__1\">Mnemonic </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5588e1_d5589e1_d5590e1__entry__2\">Explanation </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5588e1_d5589e1_d5590e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">color</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5588e1_d5589e1_d5590e1__entry__2\">General color calculate command. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5588e1_d5589e1_d5590e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">color_<var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var>\n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5588e1_d5589e1_d5590e1__entry__2\">Set to color combination <var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var>, where\n                  <var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var> is an index color identifer from 0 through 63. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gox1665702984604__section_zbv_ldn_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d627400e122\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gox1665702984604__p_d63893e1_d63894e1_d63895e1\">If it is possible, use the <code class=\"ph codeph\">color</code>\n        mnemonic to generate (or disable) all colors using a single command. Include the parameter\n        %p in the output string to represent the color number Uniface wants. For more information,\n        see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mzr1665702983304.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mzr1665702983304.html\" title=\"Some mnemonics include parameters in the output sequence that can be used to determine layout and formatting information, such as horizontal and vertical coordinates, numeric base zero (decimal, octal, or hexadecimal), zero padding, and so on. The output sequence can even include expressions that use the parameters incalculation, for example, to increment values.\">Parameters in the Output Sequence</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gox1665702984604__p_d63896e1_d63897e1_d63898e1\">Each of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">color_</code> definitions\n        corresponds to one of the 64 color combinations (numbered 0 through 63) available. The\n        definition for each color number defines both the foreground and background color. The\n        definition for <code class=\"ph codeph\">color_0</code> corresponds to the default color combination\n        selected at the start of the session, and is also used to reset from a color. If both the\n        general color mnemonic and a specific <code class=\"ph codeph\">color_</code> mnemonic are defined, the\n        specific mnemonic takes priority.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gox1665702984604__p_d63899e1_d63900e1_d63901e1\">The device translation tables supplied with Uniface use\n        the values shown in the table for determining the 64 color combinations. When you define a\n        device translation table, you are advised to map each combination to the same pair of\n        colors. This ensures the maximum level of compatibility with the device translation tables\n        distributed with Uniface.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Default Uniface Color Codes</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__1\">Color </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__2\">Foreground Color </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__3\">Background Color </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__1\">System default </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__2\">0 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__3\">0 </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__1\">Blue </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__2\">8 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__3\">1 </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__1\">Green </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__2\">16 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__3\">2 </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__1\">Cyan </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__2\">24 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__3\">3 </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__1\">Red </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__2\">32 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__3\">4 </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__1\">Purple </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__2\">40 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__3\">5 </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__1\">Yellow </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__2\">48 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__3\">6 </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__1\">White </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__2\">\n-\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__3\">7 </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__1\">Black </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__2\">56 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gox1665702984604__table_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1__entry__3\">\n-\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"gox1665702984604__pre_b1f_pdn_hcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^BEGIN_DEVICE\n...\n’S(I%(p%8))W(I%(p/8))T’ ^COLOR\n’S(I0)W(I7)T’ ^COLOR_0\n’S(I7)W(I0)T’ ^COLOR_63\n...\n^END_DEVICE\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527948\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527948\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface Index Color Mnemonics Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface Index Color Mnemonics Color mnemonics in the table define the 64 Uniface index color combinations. Arguments Table 1. Mnemonics for Uniface Index Colors Mnemonic Explanation color General color calculate command. color_ n Set to color combination n , where n is an index color identifer from 0 through 63. Description If it is possible, use the color mnemonic to generate (or disable) all colors using a single command. Include the parameter %p in the output string to represent the color number Uniface wants. For more information, see Parameters in the Output Sequence . Each of the color_ definitions corresponds to one of the 64 color combinations (numbered 0 through 63) available. The definition for each color number defines both the foreground and background color. The definition for color_0 corresponds to the default color combination selected at the start of the session, and is also used to reset from a color. If both the general color mnemonic and a specific color_ mnemonic are defined, the specific mnemonic takes priority. The device translation tables supplied with Uniface use the values shown in the table for determining the 64 color combinations. When you define a device translation table, you are advised to map each combination to the same pair of colors. This ensures the maximum level of compatibility with the device translation tables distributed with Uniface. Table 2. Default Uniface Color Codes Color Foreground Color Background Color System default 0 0 Blue 8 1 Green 16 2 Cyan 24 3 Red 32 4 Purple 40 5 Yellow 48 6 White - 7 Black 56 - ^BEGIN_DEVICE ... ’S(I%(p%8))W(I%(p/8))T’ ^COLOR ’S(I0)W(I7)T’ ^COLOR_0 ’S(I7)W(I0)T’ ^COLOR_63 ... ^END_DEVICE Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}